    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Deuteronomy",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 24,
        "summary": "Laws are given concerning divorce, newly married persons, making merchandise of men, taking pledges, leprosy, oppression of servants, and leaving gleanings of crops.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "When a man hath taken a wife, and married her, and it come to pass that she find no favour in his eyes, because he hath found some uncleanness in her: then let him write her a bill of divorcement, and give it in her hand, and send her out of his house.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Wives.",
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0from unchastity, indecency.",
                        "start": 131,
                        "end": 142
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 1:19. TG\u00a0Divorce.",
                        "start": 184,
                        "end": 195
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 290
                    }
                ],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 206,
                        "end": 208
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And when she is departed out of his house, she may go and be another man's wife.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 75,
                        "end": 80
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And if the latter husband hate her, and write her a bill of divorcement, and giveth it in her hand, and sendeth her out of his house; or if the latter husband die, which took her to be his wife;",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 86
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 179,
                        "end": 184
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Her former husband, which sent her away, may not take her again to be his wife, after that she is defiled; for that is abomination before the Lord: and thou shalt not cause the land to sin, which the Lord thy God giveth thee for an inheritance.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0bring guilt upon the land.",
                        "start": 167,
                        "end": 172
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 118
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 225,
                        "end": 228
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "When a man hath taken a new wife, he shall not go out to war, neither shall he be charged with any business: but he shall be free at home one year, and shall cheer up his wife which he hath taken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 20:7.",
                        "start": 28,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0be happy with. TG\u00a0Family, Love within; Marriage, Husbands.",
                        "start": 158,
                        "end": 166
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 109,
                        "end": 112
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "No man shall take the nether or the upper millstone to pledge: for he taketh a man's life to pledge.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0lower.",
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0it is as if he took.",
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 84
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "If a man be found stealing any of his brethren of the children of Israel, and maketh merchandise of him, or selleth him; then that thief shall die; and thou shalt put evil away from among you.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Stealing.",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 26
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 21:14.",
                        "start": 85,
                        "end": 96
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Take heed in the plague of leprosy, that thou observe diligently, and do according to all that the priests the Levites shall teach you: as I commanded them, so ye shall observe to do.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Leprosy.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 34
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Teacher.",
                        "start": 125,
                        "end": 130
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 157,
                        "end": 159
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Remember what the Lord thy God did unto Miriam by the way, after that ye were come forth out of Egypt.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou dost lend thy brother any thing, thou shalt not go into his house to fetch his pledge.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt stand abroad, and the man to whom thou dost lend shall bring out the pledge abroad unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0outside.",
                        "start": 17,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "And if the man be poor, thou shalt not sleep with his pledge:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0keep it overnight.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 60
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 17
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "In any case thou shalt deliver him the pledge again when the sun goeth down, that he may sleep in his own raiment, and bless thee: and it shall be righteousness unto thee before the Lord thy God.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ex. 22:26; Ezek. 18:7.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 45
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0garment (also v.\u00a017).",
                        "start": 106,
                        "end": 113
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not oppress an hired servant that is poor and needy, whether he be of thy brethren, or of thy strangers that are in thy land within thy gates:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 14:31.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0of the cities, towns.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 47
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 123
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "At his day thou shalt give him his hire, neither shall the sun go down upon it; for he is poor, and setteth his heart upon it: lest he cry against thee unto the Lord, and it be sin unto thee.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0The same day.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 10
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Lev. 19:13.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 39
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 15:9.",
                        "start": 135,
                        "end": 138
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 30
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The fathers shall not be put to death for the children, neither shall the children be put to death for the fathers: every man shall be put to death for his own sin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Marriage, Fatherhood.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 11
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Punish.",
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 37
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Sam. 21:6 (1\u201314); Isa. 14:21.",
                        "start": 74,
                        "end": 82
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Accountability; Justice.",
                        "start": 156,
                        "end": 159
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sin.",
                        "start": 160,
                        "end": 163
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Thou shalt not pervert the judgment of the stranger, nor of the fatherless; nor take a widow's raiment to pledge:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 27:19.",
                        "start": 15,
                        "end": 22
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Judgment.",
                        "start": 27,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 56
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "But thou shalt remember that thou wast a bondman in Egypt, and the Lord thy God redeemed thee thence: therefore I command thee to do this thing.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "HEB\u00a0slave.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 48
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou cuttest down thine harvest in thy field, and hast forgot a sheaf in the field, thou shalt not go again to fetch it: it shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow: that the Lord thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hands.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ruth 2:2. TG\u00a0Poor; Welfare.",
                        "start": 188,
                        "end": 193
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 291
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou beatest thine olive tree, thou shalt not go over the boughs again: it shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When thou gatherest the grapes of thy vineyard, thou shalt not glean it afterward: it shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 69,
                        "end": 71
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And thou shalt remember that thou wast a bondman in the land of Egypt: therefore I command thee to do this thing.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            }
        ]
    }
}